      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_united_kingdom_model_for_end-stage_liver_disease">United Kingdom Model for End-Stage Liver Disease</xref>
 is an 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_assessment_tool">ASSESSMENT TOOL</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_united_kingdom_model_for_end-stage_liver_disease">United Kingdom Model for End-Stage Liver Disease</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_united_kingdom_model_for_end-stage_liver_disease">UKELD</xref>) is a scoring system that predicts the risk of mortality due to liver cirrhosis and is used to assess the need for liver transplantation.        </p>
      <p>
